@startuml boundary_stage_to_dcm_service_response_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Boundary Stage To DCM Service Response Signal Flow\n(route/boundary context -> DCM diagnostic service seams)

participant "NAV / alert /\nboundary context" as DiagCtx #F4F7FB
participant "DCM\ndiagnostic communication owner" as DCM #E8F7E8
participant "Diag service seams" as DiagBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / tests" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Diagnostic Inputs ==

DiagCtx -> DCM : routeActive / alertLevel\nboundaryAlive / warningPathStatus / failSafeMode
DCM -> DCM : serviceContext = ethHasBoundaryServiceContext(routeActive, alertLevel)
DCM -> DCM : diagStage = ethDiagBoundaryStage(routeActive, alertLevel, boundaryAlive, warningPathStatus, failSafeMode)
DCM -> DCM : securitySession and authState derived from serviceContext / diagStage
note right of DCM
Representative gating inputs
- routeActive
- alertLevel
- boundaryAlive
- warningPathStatus
- failSafeMode
end note

== Service-seam Publish ==

DCM -> DiagBus : Diag::ServiceState / ResponseKind / ReasonCode
DCM -> DiagBus : request/response trace sysvars via publishDcmStateTrace()
note right of DCM
Representative outputs
- ServiceState
- ResponseKind
- ReasonCode
- request/response trace context
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

DiagBus -> Obs : diagnostic service readback /\ntest verdict evidence

note over DiagCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Route and boundary context reach DCM
2. DCM derives diagnostic stage and response posture
3. DCM publishes service-state and response seams
4. Tests and observers consume the effective diagnostic response state
end note

@enduml
